public abstract class MultiLineParser

Author:
jaschasilbermann A Multi Line Parser uses a variable number of lines to parse a single object. The parser decides if a line of text describes the object currently under work or a new object via the #_isSameObject() method.

The parser returns the finished object once a line belonging to a new object is encountere. Otherwise it returns null to signal that another line is welcome.

Supple the parser with a LineParser.NEW_LINE character to flush the last object out of the parser.

CAUTION: This version of the Multi Line Parser is somewhat buggy. It probably doesn't parse the first object correctly and it most likely doesn't parse the last object at all. However, for large numbers of objects this is usually not crucial.
